: capable_of GO:0160236 ! tRNA 5-taurinomethyluridine synthase activity\nproperty_value: term_tracker_item \"https://github.com/geneontology/go-ontology/issues/30539\" xsd:anyURI\ncreated_by: dragon-ai-agent\ncreation_date: 2025-07-05T12:00:00Z\n\n[Term]\nid: GO:7770011\nname: lipid exchange activity\nnamespace: molecular_function\ndef: \"Enables the transfer of a specific lipid molecule from one membrane to another, coupled with the simultaneous counter-transfer of a different lipid molecule in the opposite direction.\" [PMID:32793602]\nis_a: GO:0120013 ! lipid transfer activity\nproperty_value: term_tracker_item \"https://github.com/geneontology/go-ontology/issues/30624\" xsd:anyURI\ncreated_by: dragon-ai-agent\ncreation_date: 2025-01-24T00:00:00Z\n\n[Term]\nid: GO:7770012\nname: negative regulation of starch biosynthetic process\nnamespace: biological_process\ndef: \"Any process that stops, prevents, or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of the chemical reactions and pathways resulting in the formation of starch.\" [PMID:26554020]\nintersection_of: GO:0065007 ! biological regulation\nintersection_of: negatively_regulates GO:0019252 ! starch biosynthetic process\nproperty_value: term_tracker_item \"https://github.com/geneontology/go-ontology/issues/30662\" xsd:anyURI\ncreated_by: dragon-ai-agent\ncreation_date: 2025-08-01T12:00:00Z\n\n[Term]\nid: GO:7770013\nname: humanin receptor complex\nnamespace: cellular_component\ndef: \"A protein complex that acts as a receptor for the neuroprotective peptide humanin (HN). In humans the receptor complex is a trimer composed of CNTFR, IL6ST and IL27RA. HN binding to IL27RA and CNTFR induces oligomerization of the three subunits.\" [PMID:19386761]\nsynonym: \"HN receptor complex\" EXACT []\nis_a: GO:0098802 ! plasma membrane signaling receptor complex\nrelationship: capable_of GO:0004888 ! transmembrane signaling receptor activity\nproperty_value: term_tracker_item \"https://github.com/geneontology/go-ontology/issues/30866\" xsd:anyURI\ncreated_by: dragon-ai-agent\n\n[Term]\nid: GO:7770014\nname: spermatid mitochondrial nucleoid elimination\nnamespace: biological_process\ndef: \"The process in which spermatids lose their mitochondrial nucleoids during spermatid development. This process involves the controlled elimination of mitochondrial DNA-protein complexes while preserving the mitochondrial membranes and and contributes to maternal mitochondrial inheritance patterns by inhibiting paternal transmission.\" [PMID:28318978]\nsynonym: \"paternal mtDNA elimination\" RELATED []\nsynonym: \"spermatid mitochondrial genome elimination\" RELATED []\nsynonym: \"spermatid nucleoid degradation\" RELATED []\nis_a: GO:0032043 ! mitochondrial DNA catabolic process\nrelationship: part_of GO:0007291 ! sperm individualization\nrelationship: part_of GO:0030382 ! sperm mitochondrion organization\nproperty_value: term_tracker_item \"https://github.com/geneontology/go-ontology/issues/30344\" xsd:anyURI\ncreated_by: dragon-ai-agent\n\n[Term]\nid: GO:7770015\nname: intermembrane lipid transporter complex\nnamespace: cellular_component\ndef: \"A protein complex that mediates the transport of lipids between membranes, in which a lipid molecule or molecules is transferred through an aqueous phase from the outer leaflet of a donor membrane to the outer leaflet of an acceptor membrane.\" [PMID:39106189, PMID:40269155]\nsynonym: \"lipid transporter complex\" RELATED []\nis_a: GO:1990351 ! transporter complex\nproperty_value: term_tracker_item \"https://github.com/geneontology/go-ontology/issues/30955\" xsd:anyURI\ncreated_by: dragon-ai-agent\n\n[Term]\nid: GO:7770016\nname: rescue of stalled mitochondrial ribosome\nnamespace: biological_process\ndef: \"A process of mitochondrial translational elongation that takes place when a mitochondrial ribosome has stalled during translation, and results in freeing the ribosome from the stalled translation complex.\" [PMID:33243891]\nis_a: GO:0070125 ! mitochondrial translational elongation\nis_a: GO:0072344 ! rescue of stalled cytosolic ribosome\nproperty_value: term_tracker_item \"https://github.com/geneontology/go-ontology/issues/30547\" xsd:anyURI\ncreated_by: dragon-ai-agent\n\n[Term]\nid: GO:7770017\nname: plasma membrane expansion\nnamespace: biological_process\ndef: \"A cellular process which results in an increase in the size (surface area) of the plasma membrane during cell growth or osmotic stress. This can occur by lipid transfer, membrane trafficking, or eisosome disassembly.\" [PMID:40629316]\nsynonym: \"plasma membrane biogenesis\" RELATED []\nis_a: GO:0007009 ! plasma membrane organization\nproperty_value: term_tracker_item \"https://github.com/geneontology/go-ontology/issues/30786\" xsd:anyURI\ncreated_by: dragon-ai-agent\n\n[Term]\nid: GO:7770018\nname: positive regulation of plasma membrane expansion\nnamespace: biological_process\ndef: \"Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of plasma membrane expansion.\" [PMID:40629316]\nintersection_of: GO:0065007 ! biological regulation\nintersection_of: positively_regulates GO:7770017 ! plasma membrane expansion\nproperty_value: term_tracker_item \"https://github.com/geneontology/go-ontology/issues/30786\" xsd:anyURI\ncreated_by: dragon-ai-agent\n\n[Term]\nid: GO:7770019\nname: negative regulation of enteroendocrine cell differentiation\nnamespace: biological_process\ndef: \"Any process that stops, prevents or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of enteroendocrine cell differentiation.\" [PMID:37883554]\nintersection_of: GO:0065007 ! biological regulation\nintersection_of: negatively_regulates GO:0035883 ! enteroendocrine cell differentiation\nproperty_value: term_tracker_item \"https://github.com/geneontology/go-ontology/issues/30979\" xsd:anyURI\ncreated_by: dragon-ai-agent\ncreation_date: 2025-10-31T00:00:00Z\n\n[Term]\nid: GO:7770020\nname: intestinal enterochromaffin enteroendocrine cell differentiation\nnamespace: biological_process\nde