eceptor activity\nnamespace: molecular_function\ndef: \"OBSOLETE. Binding specifically to a glycoprotein (cargo) to deliver it to a transport vesicle. Glycoprotein cargo receptors span membranes, binding simultaneously to cargo molecules and coat adaptors, to efficiently recruit the cargo molecules to nascent vesicles.\" [PMID:41203586]\ncomment: The reason for obsoletion is that this term was added in error. Most vesicle cargo are glycoproteins, so classifying cargo receptors by glycoprotein substrate introduces an additional, unhelpful axis of classification. Cargo receptor activities should instead be organized by transport domain (i.e., the vesicles they connect cargo to), with substrates captured via has_input.\nproperty_value: term_tracker_item \"https://github.com/geneontology/go-ontology/issues/31948\" xsd:anyURI\nis_obsolete: true\nreplaced_by: GO:0038024\n\n[Term]\nid: GO:7770029\nname: phosphatidylserine receptor activity\nnamespace: molecular_function\ndef: \"Combining with phosphatidylserine and transmitting the signal from one side of the membrane to the other to initiate a change in cell activity.\" [PMID:17960135, PMID:18082433]\nis_a: GO:0004888 ! transmembrane signaling receptor activity\nrelationship: has_part GO:0001786 ! phosphatidylserine binding\nproperty_value: term_tracker_item \"https://github.com/geneontology/go-ontology/issues/31055\" xsd:anyURI\ncreated_by: dragon-ai-agent\n\n[Term]\nid: GO:7770030\nname: rod photoreceptor phosphodiesterase 6 complex\nnamespace: cellular_component\ndef: \"A heterotetrameric cGMP phosphodiesterase complex found in the disc membranes of rod photoreceptor outer segments. It consists of two catalytic subunits, PDE6A and PDE6B, and two inhibitory gamma-subunits, PDE6G. In response to activation by transducin, the complex hydrolyzes cyclic GMP, thereby mediating the light-induced closure of cGMP-gated ion channels during rod phototransduction.\" [PMID:38159849]\nsynonym: \"rod PDE6 complex\" EXACT []\nsynonym: