anded RNA\n\n[Stefan Bauernfried](/?term=Bauernfried+S&cauthor_id=33243852)  [1](#full-view-affiliation-1 \"Gene Center and Department of Biochemistry, Ludwig-Maximilians-Universität München, Munich, Germany.\") , [Matthias J Scherr](/?term=Scherr+MJ&cauthor_id=33243852)  [2](#full-view-affiliation-2 \"Max-Planck Institute of Biochemistry, Martinsried, Germany.\") , [Andreas Pichlmair](/?term=Pichlmair+A&cauthor_id=33243852)  [3](#full-view-affiliation-3 \"Institute of Virology, Technical University of Munich, School of Medicine, Munich, Germany.\")   [4](#full-view-affiliation-4 \"German Center for Infection Research (DZIF), Munich, Germany.\") , [Karl E Duderstadt](/?term=Duderstadt+KE&cauthor_id=33243852)  [2](#full-view-affiliation-2 \"Max-Planck Institute of Biochemistry, Martinsried, Germany.\")   [5](#full-view-affiliation-5 \"Physics Department, Technical University of Munich, Garching, Germany.\") , [Veit Hornung](/?term=Hornung+V&cauthor_id=33243852)  [6](#full-view-affiliation-6 \"Gene Center and Department of Biochemistry, Ludwig-Maximilians-Universität München, Munich, Germany. hornung@genzentrum.lmu.de.\")   [2](#full-view-affiliation-2 \"Max-Planck Institute of Biochemistry, Martinsried, Germany.\")\n\nAffiliations Expand\n\n### Affiliations\n\n-   1 Gene Center and Department of Biochemistry, Ludwig-Maximilians-Universität München, Munich, Germany.\n-   2 Max-Planck Institute of Biochemistry, Martinsried, Germany.\n-   3 Institute of Virology, Technical University of Munich, School of Medicine, Munich, Germany.\n-   4 German Center for Infection Research (DZIF), Munich, Germany.\n-   5 Physics Department, Technical University of Munich, Garching, Germany.\n-   6 Gene Center and Department of Biochemistry, Ludwig-Maximilians-Universität München, Munich, Germany. hornung@genzentrum.lmu.de.\n\n-   PMID: **33243852**\n-   DOI: [10.1126/science.abd0811](https://doi.org/10.1126/science.abd0811)\n\nItem in Clipboard\n\n# Human NLRP1 is a sensor for double-stranded RNA\n\nStefan Bauernfried et al. Science. 2021.\n\nShow details\n\nDisplay options\n\nDisplay options\n\nFormat Abstract PubMed PMID\n\nScience\n\nActions\n\n-   [Search in PubMed](/?term=%22Science%22%5Bjour%5D&sort=date&sort_order=desc)\n-   [Search in NLM Catalog](https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/nlmcatalog?term=%22Science%22%5BTitle+Abbreviation%5D)\n-   [Add to Search](#)\n\n. 2021 Jan 29;371(6528):eabd0811.\n\ndoi: 10.1126/science.abd0811. Epub 2020 Nov 26.\n\n### Authors\n\n[Stefan Bauernfried](/?term=Bauernfried+S&cauthor_id=33243852)  [1](#short-view-affiliation-1 \"Gene Center and Department of Biochemistry, Ludwig-Maximilians-Universität München, Munich, Germany.\") , [Matthias J Scherr](/?term=Scherr+MJ&cauthor_id=33243852)  [2](#short-view-affiliation-2 \"Max-Planck Institute of Biochemistry, Martinsried, Germany.\") , [Andreas Pichlmair](/?term=Pichlmair+A&cauthor_id=33243852)  [3](#short-view-affiliation-3 \"Institute of Virology, Technical University of Munich, School of Medicine, Munich, Germany.\")   [4](#short-view-affiliation-4 \"German Center for Infection Research (DZIF), Munich, Germany.\") , [Karl E Duderstadt](/?term=Duderstadt+KE&cauthor_id=33243852)  [2](#short-view-affiliation-2 \"Max-Planck Institute of Biochemistry, Martinsried, Germany.\")   [5](#short-view-affiliation-5 \"Physics Department, Technical University of Munich, Garching, Germany.\") , [Veit Hornung](/?term=Hornung+V&cauthor_id=33243852)  [6](#short-view-affiliation-6 \"Gene Center and Department of Biochemistry, Ludwig-Maximilians-Universität München, Munich, Germany. hornung@genzentrum.lmu.de.\")   [2](#short-view-affiliation-2 \"Max-Planck Institute of Biochemistry, Martinsried, Germany.\")\n\n### Affiliations\n\n-   1 Gene Center and Department of Biochemistry, Ludwig-Maximilians-Universität München, Munich, Germany.\n-   2 Max-Planck Institute of Biochemistry, Martinsried, Germany.\n-   3 Institute of Virology, Technical University of Munich, School of Medicine, Munich, Germany.\n-   4 German Center for Infection Research (DZIF), Munich, Germany.\n-   5 Physics Department, Technical University of Munich, Garching, Germany.\n-   6 Gene Center and Department of Biochemistry, Ludwig-Maximilians-Universität München, Munich, Germany. hornung@genzentrum.lmu.de.\n\n-   PMID: **33243852**\n-   DOI: [10.1126/science.abd0811](https://doi.org/10.1126/science.abd0811)\n\nItem in Clipboard\n\nFull text links Cite\n\nDisplay options\n\nDisplay options\n\nFormat AbstractPubMedPMID\n\n## Abstract\n\nInflammasomes function as intracellular sensors of pathogen infection or cellular perturbation and thereby play a central role in numerous diseases. Given the high abundance of NLRP1 in epithelial barrier tissues, we screened a diverse panel of viruses for inflammasome activation in keratinocytes. We identified Semliki Forest virus (SFV), a positive-strand RNA virus, as a potent activator of human but not murine NLRP1B. SFV replication and the associated formation of double-stranded (ds) RNA was required to engage the NLRP1 inflammasome. Moreover, delivery of long dsRNA was sufficient to trigger activation. Biochemical studies revealed that NLRP1 binds dsRNA through its leucine-rich repeat domain, resulting in its NACHT domain gaining adenosine triphosphatase activity. Altogether, these results establish human NLRP1 as a direct sensor for dsRNA and thus RNA virus infection.\n\nCopyright © 2021 The Authors, some rights reserved; exclusive licensee American Association for the Advancement of Science. No claim to original U.S. Government Works.\n\n[PubMed Disclaimer](/disclaimer/)\n\n## Comment in\n\n-   [NLRP1: a jack of all trades, or a master of one?](/33545058/)\n    \n    Bachovchin DA. Bachovchin DA. Mol Cell. 2021 Feb 4;81(3):423-425. doi: 10.1016/j.molcel.2021.01.001. Mol Cell. 2021. PMID: 33545058\n    \n\n## Publication types\n\n-   Research Support, Non-U.S. Gov't\n    \n    Actions\n    \n    -   [Search in PubMed](/?term=%22Research+Support%2C+Non-U.S.+Gov%27t%22%5Bpt%5D&sort=date&sort_order=desc)\n    -   [Search in MeSH](https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/mesh?term=Research+Support%2C+Non-U.S.+Gov%27t)\n    -   [Add to Search](#)\n    \n\n## MeSH terms\n\n-   Adaptor Proteins, Signal Transducing / chemistry\n    \n    Actions\n    \n    -   [Search in PubMed](/?term=%22Adaptor+Proteins%2C+Signal+Transducing%2Fchemistry%22%5BMeSH%5D&sort=date&sort_order=desc)\n    -   [Search in MeSH](https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/mesh?term=Adaptor+Proteins%2C+Signal+Transducing)\n    -   [Add to Search](#)\n    \n-   Adaptor Proteins, Signal Transducing / metabolism\\*\n    \n    Actions\n    \n    -   [Search in PubMed](/?term=%22Adaptor+Proteins%2C+Signal+Transducing%2Fmetabolism%22%5BMAJR%5D&sort=date&sort_order=desc)\n    -   [Search in MeSH](https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/mesh?term=Adaptor+Proteins%2C+Signal+Transducing)\n    -   [Add to Search](#)\n    \n-   Adenosine Triphosphatases / chemistry\n    \n    Actions\n    \n    -   [Search in PubMed](/?term=%22Adenosine+Triphosphatases%2Fchemistry%22%5BMeSH%5D&sort=date&sort_order=desc)\n    -   [Search in MeSH](https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/mesh?term=Adenosine+Triphosphatases)\n    -   [Add to Search](#)\n    \n-   Adenosine Triphosphatases / metabolism\n    \n    Actions\n    \n    -   [Search in PubMed](/?term=%22Adenosine+Triphosphatases%2Fmetabolism%22%5BMeSH%5D&sort=date&sort_order=desc)\n    -   [Search in MeSH](https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/mesh?term=Adenosine+Triphosphatases)\n    -   [Add to Search](#)\n    \n-   Adenosine Triphosphate / metabolism\n    \n    Actions\n    \n    -   [Search in PubMed](/?term=%22Adenosine+Triphosphate%2Fmetabolism%22%5BMeSH%5D&sort=date&sort_order=desc)\n    -   [Search in MeSH](https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/mesh?term=Adenosine+Triphosphate)\n    -   [Add to Search](#)\n    \n-   Alphavirus Infections / immunology\n    \n    Actions\n    \n    -   [Search in PubMed](/?term=%22Alphavirus+Infections%2Fimmunology%22%5BMeSH%5D&sort=d